{'id': 21245974, 'body': "The savings account is a tiered variable rate account as described in our terms and conditions. The standard rate may fluctuate in line with the Federal Reserve's rate, however we try to keep the premium tier rate consistently high! We also wanted to let you know that the maximum amount allowed in your Varo Savings Account to continue qualifying for the premium rate is not $5,000. It currently remains at $10,000. You can go here to learn more! https://faq.varomoney.com/hc/en-us/articles/360050828092-How-do-I-Earn-the-Higher-Interest-Rate-or-Annual-Percentage-Yield-APY-on-my-Varo-Savings-Account-

Regarding your transfer limit frustrations, you can avoid that limit by initiating the transfer on your external bank accounts end and that will also allow the transfer to process quicker. As you build a good history with Varo, your limits will increase. If you have an immediate need, please send a message to support@varomoney.com, and our service team can help!
", 'modified': '2021-02-23T18:55:00Z'}

{'id': 19939299, 'body': "We're really sorry to hear about your experience. This definitely isn't the user experience that we designed but your feedback has been heard and we appreciate you for taking the time to leave us your honest review. 

